---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TrustedByCarousel from '../components/home/TrustedByCarousel';
import GlobeSection from '../components/home/GlobeSection';
import { MagneticCTA } from '../components/ui/magnetic-cta';
import { TextReveal } from '../components/ui/text-reveal';
import { BackgroundMesh } from '../components/ui/background-paper-shaders';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Meet the team behind Duddcash — video & photo production for brands, artists, and events.">
  <section class="about section">
    <!-- Grid texture background -->
    <svg class="about__grid" width="100%" height="100%">
      <defs>
        <pattern id="about-grid" width="40" height="40" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
          <path d="M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" />
        </pattern>
      </defs>
      <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#about-grid)" />
    </svg>
    <!-- Floating 3D icons — wrapper locks height so icons don't shift on story expand -->
    <div class="film-icons-wrap">
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--1">
        <img src="/icons/sony-a7.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--2">
        <img src="/icons/film-camera.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--3">
        <img src="/icons/clapperboard.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--4">
        <img src="/icons/director-chair.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--5">
        <img src="/icons/gimbal.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--6">
        <img src="/icons/gmaster-lens.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--7">
        <img src="/icons/macbook.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--8">
        <img src="/icons/sd-card.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--9">
        <img src="/icons/sigma-lens.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--10">
        <img src="/icons/camcorder.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--11">
        <img src="/icons/camera.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--12">
        <img src="/icons/gm-70-200.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--13">
        <img src="/icons/fuji-topdown.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--14">
        <img src="/icons/drone.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="film-icon film-icon--15">
        <img src="/icons/polaroid.png" alt="" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about__inner">
      <div class="about__header" data-animate>
        <h1 class="about__title">Our Story</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="about__text" data-animate>
        <p>
          At the age of 15, Calo Shiban picked up his first video camera. Instantly, he knew nothing could match the feeling of creating the exact shot you saw in your head. Over the next year, he poured over hundreds of movies and did his best to apply what he saw to his own short films. Using his digital media class as a springboard, he created countless short stories and comedic segments alongside his best friend, Anthony Arutyunov.
        </p>

        <input type="checkbox" id="story-toggle" class="story__checkbox" />
        <div class="story__more">
          <p>
            Their teacher, Mr. Bokovitz, loved the work they created together and introduced them to a former student, Ben Gugick, who excelled at short form advertisements mostly featured on Instagram. Ben presented the class with a variety of well shot, well paced, and well edited pieces. Calo was enamored and stayed nearly an hour after class asking how he created such strong visuals on a seemingly shoestring budget. Ben enjoyed breaking down his process and urged Calo to give him a call after school. After some hesitation, Calo finally reached out a few months later, hoping to learn as much as he could about videography and editing.
          </p>
          <p>
            During the following summer, Ben taught Calo everything he could about his approach to content creation. Shortly after, Anthony asked Calo to set up an introduction so he could learn as well. Guided by Ben, the two picked up small marketing jobs around Cleveland, working with him as much as possible to build their skills and start forming their own brand. Anthony understood the assignment almost immediately and within months felt like a seasoned editor. Calo worked to keep pace on editing while also contributing through client communication and camera direction.
          </p>
          <p>
            Despite making less than $10 an hour on most jobs, the competitive nature between them pushed both of them deeper into the world of Instagram marketing. When one made something better, the other worked harder to catch up. While the projects varied, they established themselves as some of the top nightlife creators in Cleveland before even graduating high school.
          </p>
          <p>
            Shortly before graduation, an opportunity came up that could turn their small passion projects into something more serious. Ben was contacted by FWD, the largest nightclub in Cleveland, to cover the entire summer. Headlined by artists like Machine Gun Kelly, John Summit, and Dom Dolla, it promised a packed season with full creative control. The only issue&mdash;Ben was moving to Chicago. Instead, he recommended Calo and Anthony take over as lead shooters and editors, with him overseeing edits to maintain quality. FWD agreed, shocked to learn they would be turning 18 just before the summer started.
          </p>
          <p>
            To maintain existing work, continue building relationships, and keep their parents happy, Calo and Anthony committed to a year of in person classes at Cleveland State. The plan was simple: see where the business stood after a year. But first, they had to deliver for FWD.
          </p>
          <p>
            Like before, they traded edits each weekend, constantly trying to outdo each other. Within a month, the marketing team felt confident in their decision, and the general feeling was that DUDDCASH improved with every edit. They balanced FWD with three other nightlife venues, plus any additional jobs that came in, making it their most productive and best-paying summer yet. Every paycheck went right back into the business&mdash;new cameras, computers, ND filters, gimbals, lenses. As they improved, so did their tools.
          </p>
          <p>
            The following year at Cleveland State marked a major shift. While moving into their dorm, they met Gabe, a content creator living across the hall. Just like Ben had done for them, they helped him develop as an editor. Soon after, they brought on Logan, another freshman who added drone work and strong shooting to the team.
          </p>
          <p>
            As the team grew, they tried to stay focused on school, but it became clear the work mattered more. When a Coachella afterparty edit came in with a three day turnaround, school took a back seat. That decision paid off, leading to connections with producers offering fast turn movie premiere edits&mdash;sometimes needing full delivery within 24 hours.
          </p>
          <p>
            Pressure formed results. They found that working under intense deadlines, even with little sleep, brought out some of their best work. By the end of the year, their output looked completely different from just six months prior, and their income finally reflected the effort they were putting in. Then in June 2024, they made their biggest connection yet.
          </p>
          <p>
            YadaYada Studio, led by Maddi Clarke, focuses on social content for high level brands. The pacing and style differed from what DUDDCASH typically produced, leaning more into shooting and product. Still, Maddi brought them in for a small project with Lululemon. They loved the experience, and the feeling was mutual&mdash;they kept getting brought back. This pushed their business forward in a big way and rounded out their skillset.
          </p>
          <p>
            That step led to the next move&mdash;joining Ben in Chicago.
          </p>
          <p>
            After training Gabe and Logan, DUDDCASH left them with every Cleveland connection they had built and made the move. Both remain key parts of the team, stepping in when projects require more hands.
          </p>
          <p>
            The duo continues to push each other with every project, building their team and sharpening their work year after year. What started as small passion projects has turned into something real, and after just a year in Chicago, they're only getting started.
          </p>
        </div>
        <label for="story-toggle" class="story__toggle">
          <span class="story__toggle-open">Read the full story</span>
          <span class="story__toggle-close">Collapse story</span>
          <svg class="story__toggle-icon" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
          </svg>
        </label>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>

  <!-- Our Goal + Scroll indicator — with dot texture -->
  <div class="goal-zone">
    <svg class="goal-zone__grid" width="100%" height="100%">
      <defs>
        <pattern id="goal-grid" width="40" height="40" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
          <path d="M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" />
        </pattern>
      </defs>
      <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#goal-grid)" />
    </svg>

    <section class="our-goal" data-animate>
      <div class="our-goal__content">
        <h2 class="our-goal__label">Our Goal</h2>
        <p class="our-goal__text">Our goal at DUDDCASH is, simply put, to tell engaging stories with riveting visuals. Whether your company wants a fast paced, action packed advertisement, or a subtle &ldquo;do more with less&rdquo; approach, we want to help YOU achieve it. Through Storyboarding, Directing, Shooting, and/or Editing, we can be the missing piece of your puzzle. With a vast catalog of content ranging from car rallies to restaurants and even festivals, we have and will do whatever it takes to get the job done right.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="scroll-hint scroll-hint--after-goal" data-animate>
      <svg width="34" height="34" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <path d="M7 13l5 5 5-5" /><path d="M7 6l5 5 5-5" />
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Team Zone — unified background wrapper -->
  <section class="team-zone">
    <!-- Subtle shader background -->
    <div class="team-zone__shader">
      <BackgroundMesh
        client:visible
        speed={0.15}
        colors={["#b0a99e", "#9e978c", "#8a8378", "#a09890"]}
        style={{ position: "absolute", inset: 0, width: "100%", height: "100%" }}
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Soft radial glow behind cards -->
    <div class="team-zone__glow"></div>

    <!-- Meet the Team divider -->
    <section class="meet-team" data-animate>
      <div class="meet-team__inner">
        <div class="meet-team__line"></div>
        <h2 class="meet-team__heading">Meet the Team</h2>
        <div class="meet-team__line"></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Founders -->
    <section class="founders section">
      <div class="founders__inner">
        <div class="founders__grid" data-animate>
          <div class="founders__card">
            <span class="founders__card-border"></span>
            <div class="founders__card-content">
              <div class="founders__avatar founders__avatar--anthony">
              </div>
              <h3 class="founders__name">Anthony Arutyunov</h3>
              <span class="founders__role">Co-Founder</span>
              <span class="founders__specialty">Director / Editor</span>
              <img src="/icons/anthony-signature.png" alt="Anthony's signature" class="founders__signature" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="founders__card">
            <span class="founders__card-border"></span>
            <div class="founders__card-content">
              <div class="founders__avatar founders__avatar--calo">
              </div>
              <h3 class="founders__name">Calo Shiban</h3>
              <span class="founders__role">Co-Founder</span>
              <span class="founders__specialty">Director / Editor</span>
              <img src="/icons/calo-signature.png" alt="Calo's signature" class="founders__signature" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Team -->
    <section class="team section">
      <div class="team__inner">
        <div class="team__grid" data-animate>
          <div class="team__card">
            <div class="team__avatar">
              <span class="team__initials">GD</span>
            </div>
            <h4 class="team__name">Gabriel Delgado</h4>
          </div>

          <div class="team__card team__card--featured">
            <div class="team__avatar">
              <span class="team__initials">LM</span>
            </div>
            <h4 class="team__name">Logan Murray</h4>
            <p class="team__bio">Traveling videographer, editor and drone pilot passionate about putting quality first. Built his career on nightlife and has since expanded to cover almost every niche — with notable collaborations including Myles Garrett and Tee Higgins, plus nightclubs across the country from Miami to Las Vegas.</p>
            <div class="team__links">
              <a href="https://www.instagram.com/loganmurrayproductions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="team__link">IG: @loganmurrayproductions</a>
              <span class="team__email">loganmurrayproduction@gmail.com</span>
            </div>
            <div class="team__signature">
              <img src="/logan-murray-signature.png" alt="Logan Murray signature" class="team__signature-img" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="team__card">
            <div class="team__avatar">
              <span class="team__initials">JJ</span>
            </div>
            <h4 class="team__name">Jayden Jones</h4>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Scroll indicator to Globe -->
    <div class="scroll-hint scroll-hint--team-bottom" data-animate>
      <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <path d="M7 13l5 5 5-5" /><path d="M7 6l5 5 5-5" />
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Globe -->
  <GlobeSection client:visible />

  <!-- Trusted By -->
  <TrustedByCarousel client:visible />

  <!-- Ready to Work — bordered container -->
  <section class="about-cta-section">
    <div class="about-cta-card">
      <div class="about-cta-card__border"></div>
      <div class="about-cta-card__inner">
        <!-- Shader background -->
        <div class="about-cta-card__shader">
          <BackgroundMesh
            client:visible
            speed={0.2}
            colors={["#e8e4dc", "#d4cfc6", "#c8c0b4", "#ddd8cf"]}
            style={{ position: "absolute", inset: 0, width: "100%", height: "100%" }}
          />
        </div>

        <!-- Grid overlay -->
        <svg class="about-cta-card__grid" width="100%" height="100%">
          <defs>
            <pattern id="cta-grid" width="40" height="40" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <path d="M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" />
            </pattern>
          </defs>
          <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#cta-grid)" />
        </svg>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="about-cta-card__content" data-animate>
          <TextReveal
            client:visible
            text="Still scrolling?"
            staggerDelay={0.1}
            initialDelay={0.1}
            style={{
              fontFamily: "var(--font-display)",
              fontSize: "clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3.5rem)",
              fontWeight: 500,
              letterSpacing: "-0.025em",
              lineHeight: 1.1,
              color: "var(--color-text)",
            }}
          />
          <p class="about-cta-card__sub">We're flattered. Let's work.</p>
          <div class="about-cta-card__buttons">
            <MagneticCTA client:visible href="/contact">Get in Touch</MagneticCTA>
            <MagneticCTA client:visible href="/#portfolio">See the Work</MagneticCTA>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: clamp(2.5rem, 5vh, 4rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(1rem, 2vh, 1.5rem);
    overflow-x: clip;
  }

  .about__grid {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    opacity: 0.06;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .about__inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 clamp(2rem, 6vw, 7rem);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about__header {
    margin-bottom: clamp(1.5rem, 3vh, 2.5rem);
  }

  .about__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text);
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: clamp(0.8rem, 1.5vh, 1.2rem);
  }

  .about__title::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 48px;
    height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(160, 140, 110, 0.7), transparent);
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  .about__text {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .about__text p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.9;
    letter-spacing: 0.005em;
  }

  .about__text p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  /* Story expand toggle */
  .story__checkbox {
    display: none;
  }

  .story__more {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  }

  .story__checkbox:checked ~ .story__more {
    max-height: 4000px;
  }

  .story__checkbox:checked ~ .story__toggle .story__toggle-open {
    display: none;
  }

  .story__checkbox:checked ~ .story__toggle .story__toggle-close {
    display: inline;
  }

  .story__checkbox:checked ~ .story__toggle .story__toggle-icon {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .story__toggle {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding: 10px 22px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(160, 140, 110, 0.25);
    background: rgba(160, 140, 110, 0.06);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease;
  }

  .story__toggle:hover {
    border-color: rgba(160, 140, 110, 0.45);
    background: rgba(160, 140, 110, 0.1);
  }

  .story__toggle-open,
  .story__toggle-close {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: #444;
  }

  .story__toggle-close {
    display: none;
  }

  .story__toggle-icon {
    color: rgba(140, 120, 90, 0.6);
    transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  }

  /* ─── Goal Zone — dot texture wrapper ─── */
  .goal-zone {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .goal-zone__grid {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    opacity: 0.06;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .goal-zone .our-goal,
  .goal-zone .scroll-hint {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  /* ─── Our Goal ─── */
  .our-goal {
    padding: clamp(1rem, 2vh, 1.5rem) clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 4rem);
  }

  .our-goal__content {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    background: #0b0b0b;
    border-radius: 23px;
    padding: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem) clamp(2rem, 5vw, 5rem);
  }

  .our-goal__label {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .our-goal__text {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    max-width: 620px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Floating 3D icons */
  .film-icons-wrap {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100vh;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .film-icon {
    position: absolute;
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .film-icon img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: contain;
    opacity: 0.95;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1));
  }

  /* Sony A7 */
  .film-icon--1 {
    width: 72px;
    top: 26.6%;
    left: 21.7%;
    animation: floatIcon1 9s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Vintage film camera */
  .film-icon--2 {
    width: 55px;
    top: 40.2%;
    left: 14.9%;
    animation: floatIcon2 11s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Clapperboard */
  .film-icon--3 {
    width: 50px;
    top: 10.0%;
    left: 19.7%;
    animation: floatIcon3 13s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Director chair */
  .film-icon--4 {
    width: 48px;
    top: 46.7%;
    left: 76.0%;
    animation: floatIcon1 8s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  /* Gimbal */
  .film-icon--5 {
    width: 44px;
    top: 24.7%;
    left: 8.0%;
    animation: floatIcon3 10s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  /* G-Master lens */
  .film-icon--6 {
    width: 52px;
    top: 29.8%;
    left: 76.5%;
    animation: floatIcon2 12s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* MacBook */
  .film-icon--7 {
    width: 58px;
    top: 22.1%;
    left: 87.8%;
    animation: floatIcon1 14s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* SD card */
  .film-icon--8 {
    width: 34px;
    top: 65.9%;
    left: 6.2%;
    animation: floatIcon2 9s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  /* Sigma lens */
  .film-icon--9 {
    width: 42px;
    top: 56.6%;
    left: 16.2%;
    animation: floatIcon3 11s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Camcorder */
  .film-icon--10 {
    width: 50px;
    top: 39.3%;
    left: 89.9%;
    animation: floatIcon1 12s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Camera */
  .film-icon--11 {
    width: 46px;
    top: 9.6%;
    left: 74.3%;
    animation: floatIcon2 10s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  /* GM 70-200mm lens */
  .film-icon--12 {
    width: 56px;
    top: 6.3%;
    left: 86.4%;
    animation: floatIcon1 11s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Fuji top-down */
  .film-icon--13 {
    width: 48px;
    top: 46.5%;
    left: 23.0%;
    animation: floatIcon3 9s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  /* Drone */
  .film-icon--14 {
    width: 60px;
    top: 45.0%;
    left: 4.7%;
    animation: floatIcon2 13s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* Polaroid */
  .film-icon--15 {
    width: 42px;
    top: 55.8%;
    left: 85.8%;
    animation: floatIcon1 10s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  @keyframes floatIcon1 {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0) rotate(0deg); }
    50% { transform: translateY(-12px) rotate(3deg); }
  }

  @keyframes floatIcon2 {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0) rotate(0deg); }
    50% { transform: translateY(10px) rotate(-2deg); }
  }

  @keyframes floatIcon3 {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0) rotate(0deg); }
    33% { transform: translateY(-8px) rotate(4deg); }
    66% { transform: translateY(6px) rotate(-3deg); }
  }

  /* Scroll hint chevrons */
  .scroll-hint {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vh, 3rem) 0 clamp(1rem, 2vh, 1.5rem);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    opacity: 0.35;
    animation: scrollBounce 2.5s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes scrollBounce {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 0.35; }
    50% { transform: translateY(6px); opacity: 0.6; }
  }

  .scroll-hint--after-goal {
    padding: 0 0 clamp(3rem, 5vh, 4rem);
    opacity: 0.5;
